PropertyDefinition.Name: Résistance au feu
PropertyDefinition.Description: Also called fire resistance. Describes the ability of a building component to maintain, for a specified period of time, fire stability (R), fire resistance (E), thermal insulation (I) and/or any other required function. In general, the fire resistance classes are expressed as follows: REI t, R t, EI t, E t, S t, where t is the period expressed in minutes.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Resistance aux balles
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the resistance of the door against bullet passage (according to STS 53.1)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Vitrage - type (simple-double-triple-quadruple)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of glass layers within the frame. E.g. "2" for double glazing.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Vitrage - Ratio de surface vitrée
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the fraction of the glazing area relative to the total area of the frame.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Seuil exterieur
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the window opening has an external sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Tablette interieure
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the window opening has an internal sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Dispositif d'occultation - automatique
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the blackout device is automatic (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Dispositif d'occultation - mobile
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the blackout device is movable (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Largeur passage net
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the net passage width.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Resistance effraction
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the resistance of the door to static and dynamic forces and human human attack.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Vitrage - transmission solaire
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the incident solar radiation that is transmitted directly through the glazing.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Type du dispositif d'occultation
PropertyDefinition.Description: Specifies the type of sun protection the door or window has.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Ventilation gap surface
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the opening area for air passage (ventilation).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Armoire avec serrure (oui/non)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the file cabinet is lockable (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Capacité (volume)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Gives the volumetric capacity of the flush.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Type de manipulation (levier, tirer, pousser, capteur)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates which type of flush the toilet is equipped with.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Est automatique
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether flushing is activated automatically after each use or periodically (TRUE) or whether manual flushing is required (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finitions - Plafonds
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the ceiling finish material if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Facteur de risque
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines, according to local building regulations, the fire risk of the space at several levels of fire hazard.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finitions - Sols
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the floor finish material in case it is not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Sprinklage
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the space is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Espace de sortie de secours
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether this space is an emergency exit (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Accès - accessibilité aux handicapés
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the element is designed to be accessible to the disabled (TRUE) or not (FALSE). This information is often used to declare the need for disabled access or for special design constraints.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Accès - Accessible au public
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indication whether this space (in case of e.g., a toilet) is designed to serve as a publicly accessible space, e.g., for a public toilet (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Hauteur de passage requise
PropertyDefinition.Description: Headroom required for the activity assigned to this space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Nombre occupants prévus
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of people required for the activity assigned to this space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Usage type de l'espace
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines the intended use of the space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finition - Plinthes
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the material of the skirting boards if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Epaisseur finition mur (exigence)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the thickness of the wall finish material if it is not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finitions - Murs
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the wall finish material if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Contrôle d'accès
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the door is equipped with door access control (badge or code, etc.) (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Ouverture motorisée
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the door is equipped with automatic closing (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: Accessoires de toit (cheminée, gouttière, passage) - propriétés

PropertyDefinition.Name: Cheminée : nombre de conduits
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of the chimney drafts, continuous holes in the chimney through which the air passes.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Type d'ouverture
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indication of the requirement of types of window panel operations. Note : although there is an "IfcWindowPanelProperties" property, some softwares do not export sub-component properties. This property has therefore been transferred to the global element.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Lieu d'assemblage de l'escalier
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates where the assembly of the element should take place, either in the factory or on site.
